{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":200,"text":"Today I'm going to talk about work."},{"time":3130,"text":"And the question I want to ask\nand answer is this:"},{"time":6190,"text":"\"Why do we work?\""},{"time":9140,"text":"Why do we drag ourselves\nout of bed every morning"},{"time":13070,"text":"instead of living our lives"},{"time":15110,"text":"just filled with bouncing from one\nTED-like adventure to another?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20190,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22010,"text":"You may be asking yourselves\nthat very question."},{"time":25090,"text":"Now, I know of course,\nwe have to make a living,"},{"time":27210,"text":"but nobody in this room thinks\nthat that's the answer to the question,"},{"time":31060,"text":"\"Why do we work?\""},{"time":32110,"text":"For folks in this room,\nthe work we do is challenging,"},{"time":36110,"text":"it's engaging, it's stimulating,\nit's meaningful."},{"time":40020,"text":"And if we're lucky,\nit might even be important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43160,"text":"So, we wouldn't work\nif we didn't get paid,"},{"time":45170,"text":"but that's not why we do what we do."},{"time":48050,"text":"And in general,"},{"time":49100,"text":"I think we think that material rewards\nare a pretty bad reason"},{"time":52170,"text":"for doing the work that we do."},{"time":54100,"text":"When we say of somebody\nthat he's \"in it for the money,\""},{"time":58140,"text":"we are not just being descriptive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61020,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62100,"text":"Now, I think this is totally obvious,"},{"time":64130,"text":"but the very obviousness of it\nraises what is for me"},{"time":67120,"text":"an incredibly profound question."},{"time":69230,"text":"Why, if this is so obvious,"},{"time":72050,"text":"why is it that for the overwhelming\nmajority of people on the planet,"},{"time":78060,"text":"the work they do\nhas none of the characteristics"},{"time":82020,"text":"that get us up and out of bed\nand off to the office every morning?"},{"time":86210,"text":"How is it that we allow\nthe majority of people on the planet"},{"time":90110,"text":"to do work that is monotonous,\nmeaningless and soul-deadening?"},{"time":95110,"text":"Why is it that as capitalism developed,"},{"time":98080,"text":"it created a mode of production,\nof goods and services,"},{"time":101130,"text":"in which all the nonmaterial satisfactions\nthat might come from work were eliminated?"},{"time":108090,"text":"Workers who do this kind of work,"},{"time":110110,"text":"whether they do it in factories,\nin call centers,"},{"time":113070,"text":"or in fulfillment warehouses,"},{"time":115190,"text":"do it for pay."},{"time":117190,"text":"There is certainly no other earthly reason\nto do what they do except for pay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123010,"text":"So the question is, \"Why?\""},{"time":126000,"text":"And here's the answer:"},{"time":128160,"text":"the answer is technology."},{"time":131110,"text":"Now, I know, I know --"},{"time":132200,"text":"yeah, yeah, yeah, technology, automation\nscrews people, blah blah --"},{"time":136090,"text":"that's not what I mean."},{"time":137210,"text":"I'm not talking about\nthe kind of technology"},{"time":140130,"text":"that has enveloped our lives,\nand that people come to TED to hear about."},{"time":144130,"text":"I'm not talking about\nthe technology of things,"},{"time":147120,"text":"profound though that is."},{"time":149110,"text":"I'm talking about another technology."},{"time":151100,"text":"I'm talking about the technology of ideas."},{"time":155050,"text":"I call it, \"idea technology\" --"},{"time":157140,"text":"how clever of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158220,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":160030,"text":"In addition to creating things,\nscience creates ideas."},{"time":164150,"text":"Science creates ways of understanding."},{"time":167130,"text":"And in the social sciences,"},{"time":169080,"text":"the ways of understanding that get created\nare ways of understanding ourselves."},{"time":174070,"text":"And they have an enormous influence\non how we think, what we aspire to,"},{"time":178140,"text":"and how we act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180040,"text":"If you think your poverty\nis God's will, you pray."},{"time":184050,"text":"If you think your poverty is the result\nof your own inadequacy,"},{"time":188170,"text":"you shrink into despair."},{"time":191120,"text":"And if you think your poverty is\nthe result of oppression and domination,"},{"time":195220,"text":"then you rise up in revolt."},{"time":197230,"text":"Whether your response to poverty\nis resignation or revolution,"},{"time":202030,"text":"depends on how you understand\nthe sources of your poverty."},{"time":205210,"text":"This is the role that ideas play\nin shaping us as human beings,"},{"time":211110,"text":"and this is why idea technology may be\nthe most profoundly important technology"},{"time":217050,"text":"that science gives us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219100,"text":"And there's something special\nabout idea technology,"},{"time":223120,"text":"that makes it different\nfrom the technology of things."},{"time":226040,"text":"With things, if the technology sucks,"},{"time":229190,"text":"it just vanishes, right?"},{"time":232000,"text":"Bad technology disappears."},{"time":234120,"text":"With ideas --"},{"time":236020,"text":"false ideas about human beings\nwill not go away"},{"time":241060,"text":"if people believe that they're true."},{"time":244230,"text":"Because if people believe\nthat they're true,"},{"time":247110,"text":"they create ways of living\nand institutions"},{"time":250160,"text":"that are consistent\nwith these very false ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254020,"text":"And that's how the industrial revolution\ncreated a factory system"},{"time":258050,"text":"in which there was really nothing you\ncould possibly get out of your day's work,"},{"time":262200,"text":"except for the pay at the end of the day."},{"time":265080,"text":"Because the father --\none of the fathers"},{"time":267070,"text":"of the Industrial Revolution,\nAdam Smith --"},{"time":269130,"text":"was convinced that human beings\nwere by their very natures lazy,"},{"time":273110,"text":"and wouldn't do anything\nunless you made it worth their while,"},{"time":276120,"text":"and the way you made it worth their while"},{"time":278120,"text":"was by incentivizing,\nby giving them rewards."},{"time":281120,"text":"That was the only reason\nanyone ever did anything."},{"time":284070,"text":"So we created a factory system consistent\nwith that false view of human nature."},{"time":289220,"text":"But once that system\nof production was in place,"},{"time":292190,"text":"there was really no other way\nfor people to operate,"},{"time":295190,"text":"except in a way that was consistent\nwith Adam Smith's vision."},{"time":300150,"text":"So the work example is merely an example"},{"time":303160,"text":"of how false ideas\ncan create a circumstance"},{"time":307220,"text":"that ends up making them true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311140,"text":"It is not true"},{"time":313160,"text":"that you \"just can't get\ngood help anymore.\""},{"time":317210,"text":"It is true"},{"time":319120,"text":"that you \"can't get good help anymore\""},{"time":322040,"text":"when you give people work to do\nthat is demeaning and soulless."},{"time":327030,"text":"And interestingly enough, Adam Smith --"},{"time":329100,"text":"the same guy who gave us\nthis incredible invention"},{"time":333070,"text":"of mass production, and division of labor"},{"time":335180,"text":"-- understood this."},{"time":336230,"text":"He said, of people who worked\nin assembly lines,"},{"time":340180,"text":"of men who worked\nin assembly lines, he says:"},{"time":342210,"text":"\"He generally becomes as stupid as it is\npossible for a human being to become.\""},{"time":349170,"text":"Now, notice the word here is \"become.\""},{"time":351200,"text":"\"He generally becomes as stupid as it is\npossible for a human being to become.\""},{"time":357230,"text":"Whether he intended it or not,\nwhat Adam Smith was telling us there,"},{"time":361130,"text":"is that the very shape of the institution\nwithin which people work"},{"time":365040,"text":"creates people who are fitted\nto the demands of that institution"},{"time":369140,"text":"and deprives people of the opportunity"},{"time":372040,"text":"to derive the kinds of satisfactions\nfrom their work that we take for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377100,"text":"The thing about science --\nnatural science --"},{"time":380100,"text":"is that we can spin fantastic\ntheories about the cosmos,"},{"time":384220,"text":"and have complete confidence"},{"time":386170,"text":"that the cosmos is completely\nindifferent to our theories."},{"time":391000,"text":"It's going to work the same damn way"},{"time":393020,"text":"no matter what theories\nwe have about the cosmos."},{"time":396230,"text":"But we do have to worry about\nthe theories we have of human nature,"},{"time":402090,"text":"because human nature will be changed\nby the theories we have"},{"time":407170,"text":"that are designed to explain\nand help us understand human beings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411170,"text":"The distinguished anthropologist,\nClifford Geertz, said, years ago,"},{"time":416150,"text":"that human beings\nare the \"unfinished animals.\""},{"time":420040,"text":"And what he meant by that\nwas that it is only human nature"},{"time":424220,"text":"to have a human nature"},{"time":426140,"text":"that is very much the product\nof the society in which people live."},{"time":431010,"text":"That human nature,\nthat is to say our human nature,"},{"time":434120,"text":"is much more created\nthan it is discovered."},{"time":438100,"text":"We design human nature"},{"time":440150,"text":"by designing the institutions\nwithin which people live and work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445080,"text":"And so you people --"},{"time":446220,"text":"pretty much the closest I ever get\nto being with masters of the universe --"},{"time":451040,"text":"you people should be asking\nyourself a question,"},{"time":455020,"text":"as you go back home\nto run your organizations."},{"time":458060,"text":"Just what kind of human nature\ndo you want to help design?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":462140,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465090,"text":"Thanks."}]}]}